donor_name: UNDP AS ADMINISTRATIVE AGENT FOR A JOINT PROGRAMME PASS THROUGH ARRANGEMENT
outputs.output_descr:
The programmes comprises of three main outputs  or pillars for which three different United Nations agencies are responsible. These are (1)  Wealth Creation, Employment and Economic Empowerment - International Labor Organisation, (2) Social Services and Reduction of Maternal, Newborn Mortality - United Nations Family Planning Agency, and (3) National Capacity for Development Management - United Nations Development Program.
Pillar 2 for which United Nations Development Program is responsible for will deliver the following outputs:  
(i) Strengthened Mkuza Monitoring System, (ii) Strengthened capacity for implementation of core reforms and aid coordination, and (iii) Effective participation of Ministeries, Departments and Agencies and Non State Actors in Policy Dialogue and Public Expenditure Review  process
